## `<file-level: imports>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-locks-1 -->

### Purpose
Tests for `sqlite_fs.locks.LockManager` — the in-memory advisory-lock registry. No Filesystem, no SQLite needed. Tests instantiate `LockManager` directly.

### Implementation Notes

```python
import pytest

from sqlite_fs.locks import LockManager, LockOp, FlockOp
from sqlite_fs.errors import LockConflict
```

---

## `test_posix_acquire_unconflicted()`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-locks-2 -->

### Purpose
Exclusive lock on a free inode succeeds and is recorded.

### Postconditions

```python
lm = LockManager()
lm.posix_lock(inode=1, fd_id=10, pid=1000, op="exclusive", start=0, length=0)
q = lm.posix_getlk(inode=1, fd_id=10, pid=1000, start=0, length=0)
assert q is not None
assert q.type == "exclusive"
assert q.pid == 1000
```

---

## `test_posix_shared_locks_coexist()`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-locks-3 -->

### Postconditions

```python
lm = LockManager()
lm.posix_lock(inode=1, fd_id=10, pid=1000, op="shared", start=0, length=0)
# Different pid acquires shared on same range: OK.
lm.posix_lock(inode=1, fd_id=20, pid=2000, op="shared", start=0, length=0)
```

