## `test_getlk_returns_conflicting_lock()`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-locks-18 -->

### Purpose
When a query range is locked by another owner, `getlk` returns a `LockQuery` describing the blocking lock — `(type, pid, start, length)`.

### Postconditions

```python
lm = LockManager()
lm.posix_lock(inode=1, fd_id=10, pid=1000, op="exclusive", start=100, length=50)
q = lm.posix_getlk(inode=1, fd_id=20, pid=2000, start=0, length=200)
assert q is not None
assert q.type == "exclusive"
assert q.pid == 1000
assert q.start == 100
assert q.length == 50
```

